cs.ET, cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.NE, cs.SE

The paper discusses hardware security in the context of emerging technologies that are being developed to overcome the limitations of CMOS technology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). The paper also discusses the application of these emerging technologies to advance hardware security, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of nanowires and related transistors, which could fall under cs.AR (Architecture), and the use of 3D and 2.5D integration, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses challenges related to these emerging technologies, which could also place it in the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
